Ilicet. “ There* is an end ; ruined ! ” This, like actum est, is a formula of despair; and is tranferred from funerals. When the remains of the deceased were laid in the tomb, the persons present were sprinkled with pure water from a branch of olive or laurel, to purify them ; then they were dismissed by the Praefiea, on pronouncing the solemn word ilicet, i. e. ire licet, whence some write it illicet.
